  "texts": [
    "One further epistemic insight that the tic-tac-toe allows to stress is that the network never comes alone: it is always flanked by its accuracy, determined in the testing phase.",
    "Differently than in the cases in which the strategy is given to the machine, the way in which the neural network works can only lead to a probability of success in performing the task, not in a certainly accurate solution (uncertainty: probabilistic output).",
    "In writing this paper, we were guided by this research question: Which epistemic insights should and can be introduced to upper secondary-school students to make them aware of the AI and ML revolution?",
    "In presenting the solution to the problem of tic-tac-toe 11 Matlab interface to make a random player play 100 times against a neural network (in this specific case, the neural network chosen is trained on the matches played by two imperative algorithms) and results of the matches through the imperative procedural, the declarative logic, and the ML neural networks approaches, we have pointed out that different epistemic insights can be fostered.",
    "In particular, the epistemic insights have here the role of articulating the difference between the three approaches, hence highlighting the novelty of ML with respect to traditional approaches to programming."
  ],
